    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Social Engagement Trend Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes social media post performance over time, comparing impressions, engagement rate, post types, hashtags, and timing patterns. The goal is to uncover what drives higher engagement and how posting strategy can be optimized.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Analyze social media engagement metrics (likes, shares, comments, impressions) at the post level.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Compare engagement across post types (image, video, carousel, text).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Study timing patterns: day-of-week and time-of-day effects on engagement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Investigate the relationship between hashtag usage and reach.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Practice interpreting noisy engagement data with appropriate caution.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Social media teams publish content regularly but often lack a systematic understanding of what content format, timing, and messaging strategy drives the highest engagement. Without data-driven analysis, content calendars remain gut-driven.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Engagement rate directly correlates with organic reach on most social platforms. Understanding what drives engagement helps teams allocate production resources, schedule posts optimally, and identify content themes worth doubling down on.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We generate a realistic synthetic dataset of **2,000 social media posts** over a 12-month period with fields:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `post_id`, `date`, `day_of_week`, `hour_posted`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `platform` — Instagram, Twitter/X, LinkedIn, Facebook\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `post_type` — Image, Video, Carousel, Text\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `hashtag_count` — number of hashtags used\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `impressions`, `likes`, `comments`, `shares`\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `engagement_rate` — (likes + comments + shares) / impressions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This is a synthetically generated dataset for educational purposes. No external download is needed.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Environment Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Configuration / Constants\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N_POSTS = 2000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DATE_START = \\\"2025-01-01\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DATE_END = \\\"2025-12-31\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PLATFORMS = [\\\"Instagram\\\", \\\"Twitter/X\\\", \\\"LinkedIn\\\", \\\"Facebook\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"POST_TYPES = [\\\"Image\\\", \\\"Video\\\", \\\"Carousel\\\", \\\"Text\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Platform-specific engagement profiles\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PLATFORM_PROFILES = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Instagram\\\":  {\\\"avg_impressions\\\": 5000, \\\"eng_mult\\\": 1.2, \\\"types\\\": [0.35, 0.25, 0.30, 0.10]},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Twitter/X\\\":  {\\\"avg_impressions\\\": 3000, \\\"eng_mult\\\": 0.8, \\\"types\\\": [0.20, 0.10, 0.05, 0.65]},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"LinkedIn\\\":   {\\\"avg_impressions\\\": 2000, \\\"eng_mult\\\": 1.0, \\\"types\\\": [0.25, 0.15, 0.20, 0.40]},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Facebook\\\":   {\\\"avg_impressions\\\": 4000, \\\"eng_mult\\\": 0.9, \\\"types\\\": [0.30, 0.30, 0.15, 0.25]},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TYPE_ENG_MULTIPLIER = {\\\"Image\\\": 1.0, \\\"Video\\\": 1.4, \\\"Carousel\\\": 1.3, \\\"Text\\\": 0.7}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Each post gets realistic impressions, engagement metrics, and timing attributes. Video and Carousel posts tend to get higher engagement, while text-only posts get less on visual platforms.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(DATE_START, DATE_END, freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N_POSTS):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    platform = rng.choice(PLATFORMS, p=[0.30, 0.25, 0.20, 0.25])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    profile = PLATFORM_PROFILES[platform]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    post_type = rng.choice(POST_TYPES, p=profile[\\\"types\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    date = rng.choice(dates)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    hour = int(rng.choice([8,9,10,11,12,13,14,17,18,19,20], p=[0.05,0.10,0.12,0.12,0.15,0.10,0.08,0.08,0.08,0.07,0.05]))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    hashtag_count = int(rng.integers(0, 15))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Impressions with noise\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    impressions = max(100, int(rng.normal(profile[\\\"avg_impressions\\\"], profile[\\\"avg_impressions\\\"] * 0.4)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Base engagement rate ~3-5%\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    base_eng = 0.04 * profile[\\\"eng_mult\\\"] * TYPE_ENG_MULTIPLIER[post_type]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Timing bonus: peak hours\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if hour in [9, 10, 11, 12, 17, 18]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        base_eng *= 1.1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Hashtag effect (diminishing returns)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    hashtag_bonus = min(hashtag_count * 0.002, 0.015)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    eng_rate = np.clip(rng.normal(base_eng + hashtag_bonus, 0.015), 0.005, 0.15)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_eng = max(1, int(impressions * eng_rate))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    likes = max(0, int(total_eng * rng.uniform(0.55, 0.75)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    comments = max(0, int(total_eng * rng.uniform(0.10, 0.25)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    shares = max(0, total_eng - likes - comments)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"post_id\\\": f\\\"P{i+1:05d}\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"date\\\": pd.Timestamp(date),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"hour_posted\\\": hour,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"platform\\\": platform,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"post_type\\\": post_type,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"hashtag_count\\\": hashtag_count,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"impressions\\\": impressions,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"likes\\\": likes,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"comments\\\": comments,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"shares\\\": shares,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"total_engagement\\\": likes + comments + shares,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"] = df[\\\"total_engagement\\\"] / df[\\\"impressions\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"day_of_week\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.day_name()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"date\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset shape: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing values:\\\\n{df.isnull().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nDuplicate post_ids: {df['post_id'].duplicated().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Negative impressions: {(df['impressions'] < 0).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Engagement > impressions: {(df['total_engagement'] > df['impressions']).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Date range: {df['date'].min()} → {df['date'].max()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✅ All validation checks passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Cleaning\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The synthetic dataset is already clean. In a real scenario you would:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Remove boosted/promoted posts if analyzing organic performance only\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Handle deleted posts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Normalize metrics across platforms with different counting methods\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Remove test/draft posts\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0014\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0015\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total posts: {len(df):,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Overall avg engagement rate: {df['engagement_rate'].mean():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Median engagement rate: {df['engagement_rate'].median():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Avg impressions: {df['impressions'].mean():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nPosts by platform:\\\\n{df['platform'].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nPosts by type:\\\\n{df['post_type'].value_counts()}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0016\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Univariate Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0017\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].hist(df[\\\"impressions\\\"], bins=50, color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Impressions Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].axvline(df[\\\"impressions\\\"].median(), color=\\\"red\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\", label=f\\\"Median: {df['impressions'].median():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].hist(df[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"], bins=50, color=\\\"seagreen\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Engagement Rate Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].axvline(df[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"].median(), color=\\\"red\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\", label=f\\\"Median: {df['engagement_rate'].median():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].hist(df[\\\"hashtag_count\\\"], bins=15, color=\\\"coral\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Hashtag Count Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0018\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Bivariate / Multivariate Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Engagement rate by platform and post type\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0019\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"platform\\\", y=\\\"engagement_rate\\\", ax=axes[0], palette=\\\"Set2\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Engagement Rate by Platform\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Engagement Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.boxplot(data=df, x=\\\"post_type\\\", y=\\\"engagement_rate\\\", ax=axes[1], palette=\\\"Set3\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Engagement Rate by Post Type\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"Engagement Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0020\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Heatmap: engagement rate by platform × post type\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pivot = df.pivot_table(values=\\\"engagement_rate\\\", index=\\\"platform\\\", columns=\\\"post_type\\\", aggfunc=\\\"mean\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(pivot, annot=True, fmt=\\\".2%\\\", cmap=\\\"YlGn\\\", ax=ax, linewidths=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Avg Engagement Rate: Platform × Post Type\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0021\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"**Interpretation:** Video posts consistently achieve the highest engagement rates across platforms. Instagram leads overall, particularly for visual content formats (Image, Carousel, Video). Text posts perform relatively better on Twitter/X and LinkedIn, which are text-native platforms.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0022\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Feature-Specific Insights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Hashtag count vs engagement\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0023\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"hashtag_eng = df.groupby(\\\"hashtag_count\\\")[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"].agg([\\\"mean\\\", \\\"count\\\"]).reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.bar(hashtag_eng[\\\"hashtag_count\\\"], hashtag_eng[\\\"mean\\\"], color=\\\"steelblue\\\", alpha=0.7)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Hashtag Count\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Avg Engagement Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Average Engagement Rate by Hashtag Count\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax2 = ax.twinx()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax2.plot(hashtag_eng[\\\"hashtag_count\\\"], hashtag_eng[\\\"count\\\"], color=\\\"coral\\\", marker=\\\"o\\\", label=\\\"Post Count\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax2.set_ylabel(\\\"Number of Posts\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax2.legend(loc=\\\"upper right\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"r, p = stats.pearsonr(df[\\\"hashtag_count\\\"], df[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Pearson correlation (hashtag count vs engagement rate): r={r:.3f}, p={p:.4f}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0024\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Posting time analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0025\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"hour_stats = df.groupby(\\\"hour_posted\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_eng_rate=(\\\"engagement_rate\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_impressions=(\\\"impressions\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    posts=(\\\"post_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].bar(hour_stats[\\\"hour_posted\\\"], hour_stats[\\\"avg_eng_rate\\\"], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Avg Engagement Rate by Hour Posted\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"Hour\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Engagement Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dow_order = [\\\"Monday\\\", \\\"Tuesday\\\", \\\"Wednesday\\\", \\\"Thursday\\\", \\\"Friday\\\", \\\"Saturday\\\", \\\"Sunday\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dow = df.groupby(\\\"day_of_week\\\")[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"].mean().reindex(dow_order)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].bar(dow.index, dow.values, color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Avg Engagement Rate by Day of Week\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0026\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Statistical Checks\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Is the engagement rate difference between Video and Text posts significant?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0027\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"video_eng = df[df[\\\"post_type\\\"] == \\\"Video\\\"][\\\"engagement_rate\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"text_eng = df[df[\\\"post_type\\\"] == \\\"Text\\\"][\\\"engagement_rate\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"t_stat, p_val = stats.mannwhitneyu(video_eng, text_eng, alternative=\\\"greater\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Video avg engagement: {video_eng.mean():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Text avg engagement:  {text_eng.mean():.2%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mann-Whitney U test: U={t_stat:.1f}, p={p_val:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Result: {'Significant' if p_val < 0.05 else 'Not significant'} at α=0.05\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0028\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Visual Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Monthly engagement trend\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0029\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"monthly = df.groupby(\\\"month\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    posts=(\\\"post_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_impressions=(\\\"impressions\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_engagement_rate=(\\\"engagement_rate\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    total_engagement=(\\\"total_engagement\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(12, 8))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].plot(monthly[\\\"month\\\"], monthly[\\\"avg_impressions\\\"], marker=\\\"o\\\", color=\\\"steelblue\\\", linewidth=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Average Impressions per Post by Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Impressions\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].plot(monthly[\\\"month\\\"], monthly[\\\"avg_engagement_rate\\\"], marker=\\\"s\\\", color=\\\"seagreen\\\", linewidth=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Average Engagement Rate by Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"Engagement Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_xlabel(\\\"Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for ax in axes:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.set_xticks(range(1, 13))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0030\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Platform engagement trend over months\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt_monthly = df.groupby([\\\"month\\\", \\\"platform\\\"])[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"].mean().reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for platform in PLATFORMS:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    subset = plt_monthly[plt_monthly[\\\"platform\\\"] == platform]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.plot(subset[\\\"month\\\"], subset[\\\"engagement_rate\\\"], marker=\\\"o\\\", label=platform, linewidth=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Monthly Engagement Rate by Platform\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Engagement Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xticks(range(1, 13))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0031\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Video posts dominate engagement** across all platforms, achieving roughly 1.4× the engagement rate of image posts and 2× that of text-only posts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Instagram has the highest overall engagement rate,** consistent with its algorithm favouring visual content.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Peak posting hours (9 AM–12 PM and 5–6 PM)** show modestly higher engagement, suggesting posts during commute and lunch times perform better.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Hashtag usage shows diminishing returns.** A moderate number (5-10) improves discoverability, but excessive hashtags do not proportionally increase engagement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Carousel posts are strong performers** — nearly matching video in engagement rate, possibly due to swipe interactions boosting algorithmic signals.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Text-only posts underperform on visual platforms** but hold their own on LinkedIn and Twitter/X.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0032\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data — real social media data has much more variability and algorithmic effects.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No follower count or account-level normalization.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No content quality or copy analysis (sentiment, length, CTA presence).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No paid promotion / boosted post distinction.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Platform algorithm changes over time are not modeled.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0033\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Invest more in video and carousel content** — these formats consistently outperform across platforms.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Schedule posts during peak engagement windows** — especially late morning and early evening.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Use a moderate number of relevant hashtags** (5-10) rather than stuffing.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Tailor content format to the platform** — text-heavy on LinkedIn, visual-first on Instagram.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Track follower growth alongside engagement** — engagement without growth may indicate audience saturation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Run A/B tests on post timing and format** to isolate causal effects from observational correlations.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0034\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Comparing raw engagement counts instead of rates.** A post with 500 likes from 100K impressions is worse than 100 likes from 2K impressions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Ignoring platform context.** 3% engagement on Instagram is normal; 3% on LinkedIn is excellent.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Over-indexing on a single viral post.** One outlier can skew averages; always look at medians too.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Not accounting for audience size.** Growing accounts naturally see lower engagement rates as reach expands beyond core followers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Confusing correlation with causation.** More hashtags correlating with reach does not mean hashtags cause more reach.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0035\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Create a \\\"best time to post\\\" heatmap** with day-of-week on Y-axis and hour on X-axis, colored by avg engagement rate.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Build a composite content score** combining engagement rate, total engagement, and impressions into a single rank.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Segment posts into \\\"high performers\\\" and \\\"low performers\\\"** using median engagement rate as a threshold. What differs between the two groups?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Add a text sentiment column** (simulated) and study whether positive sentiment posts get higher engagement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Compute rolling 30-day engagement rate** and plot it as a time series to spot trend changes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"a0036\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Format matters most:** Video and Carousel posts significantly outperform text across platforms.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Timing provides a modest lift:** Posting during peak hours improves engagement but is secondary to content format.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Hashtags help, but only up to a point.** Moderate hashtag usage is optimal.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Platform-specific strategies are essential.** What works on Instagram does not necessarily work on LinkedIn.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Always use engagement rate, not raw counts,** as the primary metric for content quality comparison.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
